{"id":41108,"date":"2023-09-06T12:50:26","date_gmt":"2023-09-06T08:50:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=41108"},"modified":"2023-09-06T12:50:26","modified_gmt":"2023-09-06T08:50:26","slug":"extravagant-decorations","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/09\/06\/extravagant-decorations\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Luxury: Warning against extravagant decorations"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Safinah reported: A man prepared food for Ali ibn Abi Talib, may Allah be pleased with him, who was his guest. Fatimah said, \u201cIf only we had invited the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, to eat with us!\u201d They called for him, and he came, then he placed his hands on the door frame. When the Prophet saw the engraved curtain in the back of the house, he turned back. Fatimah told Ali, \u201cCatch up to him and see what turned him back.\u201d Ali followed him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what made you return?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It is not for myself, or a prophet, to enter a decorated house<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 3755<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0633\u064e\u0641\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0636\u064e\u0627\u0641\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0637\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0628\u064d \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0641\u064e\u0635\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0639\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u